TestReportMasksSensitiveVariables
/ Regression test for security finding #3: proves test.report routes assertion
/ failure content through DiagnosticOutput so [Sensitive] properties are masked.
/ The fixture fails with an Identity (carrying a Sensitive PrivateKey) in
/ AssertionError.Actual + the Variables snapshot. We then check the written
/ report content has the key name preserved ('privateKey') but the value
/ redacted ('******'), while the non-sensitive 'publicKey' still serializes.
/ A regression that drops the DiagnosticOutput modifier — or falls back to
/ value.ToString() — would fail the '******' assertion.
- test.discover tests in '_fixtures_sensitive', pattern='*.fixture.goal', recursive, write to %tests%
- test.run tests %tests%, write to %results%
- test.report results %results%, write to %report%
- assert %report.summaryFail% equals 1
- assert %report.content% contains 'privateKey'
- assert %report.content% contains '******'
- assert %report.content% contains 'publicKey'
